  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0d82\u0da0\u0dd2\u0dad \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0dc5\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Corporation reveals fuel reserves",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sangala Ratnayake, Chairman of the Committee appointed by the Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe to look into the existing fuel reserves of the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation, said.",
        "Accordingly, the Corporation has 11,000 metric tons of diesel, 30,000 metric tons of fuel, 800 metric tons of jet fuel and 5000 metric tons of petrol.",
        "Accordingly, it has been decided to issue diesel only for essential services in order to use the fuel owned by the Corporation safely."
      ],
